quran[13]{c,v,t}:
  18,62,"And when they had gone further, he said to his servant, \"Bring us our breakfast, for we have suffered much fatigue on this journey"
  18,63,"Said he, \"What think you? When we resorted to the rock, then, verily, I forgot the fish, but it was only Satan, who made me forget it, and I forgot to tell you; and it took its way in the sea in a marvellous way"
  18,64,"Moses said, \"This is what we were searching for.\" So they retraced their steps again"
  18,65,"Then they found a servant of Ours, to whom We had given mercy from Ourselves, and had taught him knowledge from Our Presence"
  18,66,"Said Moses to him, \"May I follow you, so that you may teach me of the (Higher) Truth which you have been taught"
  18,67,"Said he, \"Verily, you can never bear it"
  18,68,How can you be patient about what you can compass no knowledge (you cannot understand)
  18,69,"He said, \"Allah willing, you will find me patient; nor will I rebel against your bidding"
  18,70,"He said, \"Well then, if you follow me, ask me not about anything until I myself begin to mention it"
  18,71,"So they set out until when they were in the boat, he made a hole therein and scuttled it. (Moses) Said, \"Have you made a hole therein to drown the people therein? You have done a dreadful thing"
  18,72,"Said he, \"Did I not tell you, truly, you can never bear with me"
  18,73,"Moses said (pleaded), \"Rebuke me not for forgetting, and be not hard on me"
  18,74,"So they set out until they met a boy, and he killed him. Moses said, \"What! Have you killed an innocent soul who has killed no one? Verily, you have done a foul (evil) deed"